md_02_aula_2 DO YOU WORK?

	1. Does he work? And your mother, does she work too?
	2. Ah, now I see how you know all those things about Brazilian history
	3. he | she | it -> DOES
	4. She works | Does she work? | She doesn't work
	5. professor | doutor | polícial | músico | motorista de ônibus | ator/atriz | dentista | escritor | advogado | engenheiro | eletricista | pintor | garçom/garçonete | guia turístico | agente de viagem | vendedor/vendedora | cabeleireiro |jardineiro | fotógrafo | bombeiro | enfermeira | assistente
	6. Mariana, você quer ser professora também?
	7. I want to be a ...
	8. I don't know what I want to be 
	9. Eu tenho algumas(some) dúvidas
       10. Maybe we will see you in a soap opera
       11. Tourism is the job of the future. You can be a clerk in a tourism agency to learn how it works
       12. I have to go. I have many things to do
       13. don't forget. Amanhã Lucas quer mostrar-nos a casa dele
       14. Nós podemos ir no(on) fim de semana?
       15. Well, it is up to you...
     	
